cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with submodular maximization under a matroid constraint in the adaptive complexity model, which is a problem in discrete optimization. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely category. The paper also introduces a novel technique of adaptive sequencing, which involves information theory and communication complexity, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper presents an approximation algorithm with near-optimal adaptivity, which involves machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. Finally, the paper deals with parallel computation and speedups, which is related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
